    "text": "Geriatric Pharmacotherapy Case Series : GLP - 1 RA for Weight Management in Older Adults.. < b > Background : < / b > This case study reviews the use of glucagon - like peptide - 1 receptor agonists ( GLP - 1 RA ) for weight management in older adults. A 69 - year - old male patient discusses weight loss goals with his health care provider and seeks pharmacotherapy options in addition to lifestyle modifications. His medical history includes type 2 diabetes mellitus ( T2D ), coronary artery disease ( CAD ), prior coronary artery bypass graft, heart failure with reduced ejection fraction ( HFrEF ), hypertension, hyperlipidemia, and allergic rhinitis. He initiated weight loss efforts following a myocardial infarction ; however, dietary and physical activity changes alone have not resulted in substantial weight reduction. < b > Assessment : < / b > This patient is an appropriate candidate for GLP - 1 RA therapy given his T2D, obesity, CAD, and a recent elevation in serum creatinine ( SCr ).",
