    "text": "Structural insights into single - pass transmembrane receptor GC - A activation by distinct antihypertensive antibodies.. The single - pass transmembrane receptor guanylyl cyclase A ( GC - A ), also known as natriuretic peptide receptor A ( NPR - A ) or NPR1, regulates blood pressure through vasodilation and natriuresis, making it a promising therapeutic target for hypertension and heart failure. We describe two monoclonal antibodies, XX16 and REGN5308, that differentially activate GC - A. Using cryo - electron microscopy and molecular dynamics simulations, we reveal that XX16 stabilizes GC - A in an active conformation even without its ligand ANP, whereas REGN5308 requires ANP to fully promote receptor activation. Both antibodies increase ANP binding affinity to GC - A and enhance GC - A - mediated cGMP signaling, although XX16 exerts a stronger stabilizing influence on ATP and GTP binding. In a mouse model of obesity - induced hypertension, XX16",
