    "text": "Pharmacokinetic Studies and Toxicity Assessment of Nisoldipine and Cilnidipine Analogues for Drug Development.. Nisoldipine and Cilnidipine are dihydropyridine calcium channel blockers used in cardiovascular therapy. Their clinical utility is limited by low oral bioavailability and rapid metabolism. This study evaluates the pharmacokinetic profiles and acute oral toxicity of selected analogues from the Zinc database, comparing pure drugs, unformulated analogues, and optimized oral disintegrating tablet ( ODT ) formulations. Acute toxicity was assessed in Swiss albino mice ( n = 3 / group ) per OECD 423 guidelines at oral doses from 5 - 2000 mg / kg. Pharmacokinetic studies were conducted in New Zealand rabbits ( n = 6 / group ) with human - equivalent dosing. Non - compartmental analysis was used to determine Cmax, Tmax, AUC₀ - t, AUC₀ - ∞, t½, MRT, and relative bioavailability. Plasma drug concentrations were measured by validated HPLC. Data were analysed by ANO",
