    "text": "Post - exercise glucose management in type 1 diabetes : Comparing carbohydrate intake and insulin reduction strategies.. This study aimed to compare two post - exercise glucose management approaches in type 1 diabetes ( T1D ) patients using continuous subcutaneous insulin infusion. A group of 46 adults and adolescents underwent a 60 - minute ergocycling session at 60 % of their VO < sub > 2peak < / sub > at 4 p. m. After the exercise, participants were randomly assigned to post - exercise glucose management strategies : The first strategy involved a 20 % reduction in basal insulin infusion rate for 10hours, along with a 20 % reduction in the dinner insulin bolus. The second strategy consisted of consuming a post - exercise snack with 50 % of their usual insulin bolus, followed by an evening snack without insulin bolus. During the 13 - hours of recovery ( 5 - PM to 6 - AM post - exercise ), there were no significant differences between the two strategies in terms of time spent within blood glucose levels of 4. 0 - 10. 0 mmol / l ( 54. 4±26. 2 vs. 57. 7±25. 9 % ) and",
